d at the University of Iowa in the USA, Université de Provence in France, and Università degli Studi Roma Tre in Italy. The papers in this volume were presented at the first of these conferences, in Iowa City, where Bergmann taught for nearly four decades after escaping from Europe, following the dissolution of the Vienna Circle of which he had been the youngest member. There are nine philosophical papers, reminiscences of three of his students, and a complete bibliography of his published writings.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aOntologyvCongresses. 4aGustav Bergmann. 4aMetaphysik. 4aOntologie. 4aPhilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Existentialism.2bisacsh1 aBaker, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonino, Guido, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrossmann, Reinhardt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeald, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJesson, Greg, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJesson, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeiden, Carl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagalhães, Ernâni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOaklander, Nathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrilia, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSievert, Donald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTegtmeier, Erwin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTegtmeier, Erwin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilson, Fred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l